<TITLE> Tahrir number two arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 21 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion has arrested the number two of banned Islamist outfit Hizb-ut-Tahrir. The fundamentalists outfit's second-in-command, Kazi Morshedul Haque, was arrested on Tuesday night from Mohammadpur, Dhaka and handed over to Uttara Police Station on Wednesday afternoon. Nisharul Arif, additional commissioner of Uttara told bdnews24.com that RAB had handed over Haque and said that he was the second-in-command of the organisation. Md Sohail, RAB's director of legal and media affairs wing, told bdnews24.com that a detective team of the elite force arrested Haque, a real estate businessman, on Tuesday midnight. He added that Haque was handed over to police as they were investigating a case against two Hizb-ut-Tahrir members arrested from Uttara on April 18 with two petrol bombs. Police arrested Tahrir's linchpin Mahiuddin Ahmed in Dhaka on April 20. The government banned the outfit on Oct 23, 2009. Hizb-ut-Tahrir has become active recently with its activists bringing out a procession in Chittagong last week. bdnews24
